<h2>ripgrep (rg)</h2>
<p>ripgrep is a line-oriented search tool that recursively searches your current
directory for a regex pattern. By default, ripgrep will respect your .gitignore
and automatically skip hidden files/directories and binary files. ripgrep
has first class support on Windows, macOS and Linux, with binary downloads
available for <a href="https://github.com/BurntSushi/ripgrep/releases">every release</a>.
ripgrep is similar to other popular search tools like The Silver Searcher, ack
and grep.</p>
